        <!-- How calculations work -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-3">How our calculations work</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2 text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)]">
            <li><strong>Concrete volume</strong> uses <code>L&nbsp;(ft) × W&nbsp;(ft) × D&nbsp;(in ÷ 12) ÷ 27</code> to output cubic yards, then converts to bag counts using published yields (0.6&nbsp;cu&nbsp;ft per 80&nbsp;lb bag).</li>
            <li><strong>Roofing material</strong> starts with the pitched roof area (footprint × pitch multiplier), then divides by coverage per bundle, panel, or sheet.</li>
            <li><strong>Paint coverage</strong> calculates wall area minus standard door and window openings, then divides by the coverage rate (typically 350&nbsp;sq&nbsp;ft per gallon).</li>
            <li><strong>Tile quantity</strong> divides floor area by tile area, then applies a waste percentage based on pattern (grid, diagonal, or herringbone).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="border-[var(--border)]" />

        <!-- Trust pillars -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold mb-1.5">Visible formulas</h4>
